RACE.RACE_TEXT: Firecracker Sprint S. RETAMA PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 95. Stakes Purse 22050. FOR ARABIANS THREE YEAR OLDS. After paying $400 for 6th through 12th place, the $15,000 Added (From TABA HIEA) and all fees will to be divided 60% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, 3% to fifth. Weight: 125 lbs. The fi eld will be limited to (12) twelve horses. Highest career earnings at time of entry will be preferred according to official statistics provided by Equibase. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Horses not drawing a star ting position in the gate will receive a refund of the entry fee. Trophy to the winning owner. If this race fails to receive 5 or more entries, the purse monies shall be transferred to the Firecracker Distaff upon TXRC approval.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RB AFTERBURN was allowed to settled then rallied three wide on the turn, drew off in mid stretch and was kept to a drive in the end. RB NASH BASH was hustled along between rivals and set a pressured pace from the inside into the turn, was in a long drive but tired in the stretch. UPTOWN WALK THE LINE pressed the pace while two wide into the turn, was used up and gave way. WMA BADGE chased the early pace while inside, was used up then stopped. PEARLS COMET AA trailed throughout. This race was hand timed.
